Listen to me.

268
00:14:37,967 --> 00:14:40,267
You're the only one I'm going to
tell you this.

269
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:42,567
Who is the only one
who has a motive

270
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:45,567
to hurt Mayor Joaquin
and his family?

271
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:47,433
Only Boss.

272
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:51,600
He's the one who ordered Sonny
to be killed.

273
00:14:52,367 --> 00:14:55,867
He wants to silence me so he
won't be exposed.

274
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,800
He's a bad guy,
you need to catch him.

275
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,633
It's not that easy.

276
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:10,067
We need to have solid or enough
evidence

277
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:16,300
to prove that Boss is the one
who ordered to kill Sonny...

278
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:19,733
to try to kill you
and the kidnapping.

279
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:21,867
Selena...

280
00:15:22,667 --> 00:15:23,633
Is there anything?

281
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:27,300
Did Sonny give you anything?

282
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:40,567
Nothing, Miss Bobby.

283
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:43,400
I'm sorry.

284
00:15:43,933 --> 00:15:46,367
Even if I wanted to, Sonny
really doesn't want

285
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:48,033
to tell me about his job.

286
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:50,267
But believe me.

287
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,533
Boss is a bad guy.

288
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,600
Believe me.

289
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:02,733
<i> Dr. Cabral,</i>

290
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:05,500
<i>please proceed
to the emergency room.</i>

291
00:16:21,967 --> 00:16:23,233
<i> Paging Dr. Gutierrez.</i>

292
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:25,533
<i>Please proceed
to the operating room.</i>

293
00:16:35,133 --> 00:16:36,700
Sir, is Sir Eric there?

294
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,167
Because my goods were spilled.

295
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,900
- Who will pay for this?
- Ms. Abi.

296
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,133
Did you see Boss Tonyo there?

297
00:16:44,433 --> 00:16:46,533
I didn't seem to notice.

298
00:16:46,667 --> 00:16:47,867
Why are you carrying
a tray of eggs?

299
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,133
Oh, this?

300
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,700
Because the Mayor is giving away
free eggs.

301
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,833
Do you want to get some?
That's big savings

302
00:16:53,967 --> 00:16:55,800
I can't because I'm waiting
for Sir Eric.

303
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:57,200
My goods were spilled.

304
00:16:57,333 --> 00:16:58,600
Someone has to pay for that.

305
00:16:58,733 --> 00:16:59,867
Too bad.

306
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:01,867
- Sir Eric.
- Oh?

307
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,500
My goods were spilled.

308
00:17:03,633 --> 00:17:04,633
Who will pay for that?

309
00:17:04,767 --> 00:17:06,267
How's my income for today?

310
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,867
Don't worry,
when Daga comes out,

311
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,067
I'll have him pay
for your goods.

312
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,933
After all, he's the one
who bumped into you.

313
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:14,267
That's good. Right.

314
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,533
Oh, Sir, have you seen
the gunman

315
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:18,433
who went on a road rage rampage
in Milagros?

316
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,200
The one who shot the riders,

317
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:21,833
- has he been caught?
- Oh, right, I saw that.

318
00:17:21,967 --> 00:17:23,633
Mar and Abdul said

319
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:27,067
that the gunman is loitering
around here.

320
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,133
Did they recognize him?

321
00:17:28,267 --> 00:17:31,200
Yes, Sir, they recognized him.

322
00:17:35,867 --> 00:17:37,167
Oh, what, let's go inside.

323
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:38,100
Get in line, okay,

324
00:17:38,233 --> 00:17:39,667
so you can get a tray of eggs,
okay?

325
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:40,633
Yes, there is.

326
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:43,333
Just say Mar's name, okay?

327
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:44,833
Yes.

328
00:17:44,967 --> 00:17:46,767
Oh, Sir, why?

329
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,800
Oh, someone told me

330
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:52,867
that you know the one shot the
riders at Milagros.

331
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,567
Oh, no, Sir,

332
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,200
but we recognize him.

333
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:59,500
Yes, Sir. Besides,
we're not close.

334
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:01,833
So, did you see him?

335
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:05,867
Actually, smooth, tall.

336
00:18:06,467 --> 00:18:07,933
Sir, that's the kind of creature

337
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:09,633
that Mar and I saw.

338
00:18:09,767 --> 00:18:12,667
Yes, and his lips
were slightly rosy

339
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:16,700
and shining,
shimmering with saliva!

340
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:18,100
- Isn't that right?
- Yes.

341
00:18:18,233 --> 00:18:19,867
Sir, that's all, yes.

342
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,800
You seem to have memorized
his appearance,

343
00:18:22,967 --> 00:18:24,133
every corner of his face.

344
00:18:24,267 --> 00:18:25,933
You seem to be dreaming
about him.

345
00:18:26,067 --> 00:18:27,667
- He's so handsome.
- Actually, I dreamt about him.

346
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,100
- Oh, ah, Sir, well...
- Oh...

347
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,100
Can we invite you
to the precinct

348
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:34,700
so we can cartographically
sketch the suspect?

349
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,733
Okay, okay, yes.

350
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:39,100
- Okay, I'm coming too.
- Yes.

351
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:40,633
- Just stay here.
- I'm coming with you.

352
00:18:40,767 --> 00:18:42,000
Hi, officer.

353
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:43,900
- Hello.
- Hello.

354
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:46,133
Hurry up, come on.

355
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:47,567
This is them, Sir.

356
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,533
This is the one taken
in our parking lot.

357
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,067
- Hey, I'm nervous.
- Me, too.

358
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,233
- Act like a man.
- Abdul, Mar.

359
00:19:34,367 --> 00:19:35,700
- Chief.
- Hello, Sir.

360
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:39,567
This is the composite sketch of
the suspect you mentioned.

361
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:42,933
It's him, Mysterious Oppa.

362
00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:46,000
Yes, it's like
I'm right in front of him.

363
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:47,533
Oh, hi, Baby...

364
00:19:47,667 --> 00:19:48,567
Actually, I missed him.

365
00:19:48,700 --> 00:19:49,733
- He's so handsome, right?
- Yes.

366
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:50,933
Yes, we met.

367
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:52,100
- My baby.
- Hello.

368
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:53,267
That guy's dangerous.

369
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,367
What?

370
00:19:54,733 --> 00:19:59,133
He killed two police officers
and five riders at close range.

371
00:19:59,267 --> 00:20:02,633
He's also a sniper
and highly skilled in combat.

372
00:20:03,367 --> 00:20:06,367
So you shouldn't
find him handsome

373
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:08,267
because he's a monster.

374
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,967
You should find me good-looking

375
00:20:10,100 --> 00:20:12,833
because I'm a monster in terms
of handsomeness.

376
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:15,333
Conde sent me photos
of the shooter

377
00:20:15,467 --> 00:20:18,400
Please identify if that
foreigner is really him.

378
00:20:18,867 --> 00:20:20,667
Chief, is that him?

379
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,567
Is Oppa in the hospital?

380
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:23,700
Has he been caught?

381
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:26,167
Unfortunately, he escaped

382
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,400
a few hours ago
after his operation.

383
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:31,533
What? Did he escape from Conde?

384
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:34,300
Conde is something else.

385
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,933
Lieutenant Conde did enough.

386
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:40,333
Let's just be thankful that he
and Enriquez are alive.

387
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,567
But Conde mentioned to me

388
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,267
that the shooter passed by here

389
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:48,100
before heading to the safehouse,

390
00:20:48,233 --> 00:20:49,800
and I confirmed it.

391
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,200
I checked the CCTV.

392
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,767
Wait a minute, Chief.

393
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:57,333
Why did the suspect
come to the precinct?

394
00:20:57,467 --> 00:20:59,000
What's his purpose?

395
00:20:59,567 --> 00:21:01,367
That's what I want to know.

396
00:21:02,833 --> 00:21:03,800
Robles...

397
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,867
based on the footage,

398
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,867
you approached him

399
00:21:09,033 --> 00:21:11,400
and spoke to the shooter.

400
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:13,200
What was his motive?

401
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,867
How did they escape, Sir?

402
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:21,200
Someone helped him.

403
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,467
What Selena said must be true.

404
00:21:29,133 --> 00:21:29,867
Why?

405
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:32,467
Selena confided in me earlier,

406
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:36,333
and she identified Sonny's
coworker

407
00:21:36,767 --> 00:21:38,367
is the deceased assassin.

408
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:40,967
And the one they're pointing to
as their boss

409
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:44,133
and mastermind in the case
we're investigating

410
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:48,067
is none other than
Victor Santiago.

411
00:21:54,667 --> 00:21:56,200
Sir, the suspect entered the
precinct

412
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:57,367
as if he were
looking for someone.

413
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,033
I approached him and asked him,

414
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:01,500
but he didn't tell me anything.

415
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:04,033
Don't you remember his face

416
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:07,233
when the viral video of his
shooting came out?

417
00:22:08,233 --> 00:22:10,033
Sir, I didn't expect the suspect

418
00:22:10,167 --> 00:22:11,967
to go to the precinct.

419
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:14,033
I'm sorry, Chief,

420
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:17,467
but he's so gutsy.

421
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:20,700
Well,

422
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:24,100
me too, I can't imagine
why he would come here.

423
00:22:26,333 --> 00:22:29,200
But, Chief, I think...

424
00:22:29,333 --> 00:22:30,367
this is my idea.

425
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:35,267
Couldn't the suspect have come
to the precinct

426
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,867
because he was looking
for Selena?

427
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:41,333
And he wanted to kill Selena.

428
00:22:41,467 --> 00:22:42,800
Because if I were the killer,

429
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:47,033
I would kill everyone
who knows me, right?

430
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:49,800
Wait, wait.
Isn't that scary?

431
00:22:49,967 --> 00:22:51,367
Well, the gunman got away.

432
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:53,567
Maybe he's loitering around our
area.

433
00:22:54,033 --> 00:22:54,867
What about us, Mar?

434
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,100
Chief, he might know us.

435
00:22:58,233 --> 00:23:00,233
Maybe he'll come back

436
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:02,433
and say, Chief,

437
00:23:02,567 --> 00:23:05,367
we were the ones who reported
him, that's why he got caught.

438
00:23:05,500 --> 00:23:09,667
Maybe we can get into the
witness protection program?

439
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,267
Yes, help us.

440
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,567
Based on what I gathered,

441
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:15,600
I'm sorry, but you aren't
qualified

442
00:23:15,733 --> 00:23:18,233
to be under witness protection

443
00:23:18,367 --> 00:23:20,367
because the suspect didn't give
you direct a threat of death

444
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:23,067
or bodily harm to you.

445
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:25,133
I'm sorry.

446
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:30,533
Chief, we're scared.

447
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,200
Why? Does she have evidence?

448
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:37,000
She doesn't have evidence yet,

449
00:23:38,067 --> 00:23:43,633
but Selena told me she saw Boss
and Sonny talking

450
00:23:43,767 --> 00:23:46,067
the day before the kidnapping.

451
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:51,800
Anyone can talk
to Victor Santiago

452
00:23:51,933 --> 00:23:54,267
because he's a public figure.

453
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:56,533
But you know, Sir,

454
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:58,600
I've had a hunch for a long time

455
00:23:58,733 --> 00:24:00,433
that Boss is involved in this.

456
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:05,167
Well, Selena just confirmed it
to me earlier.

457
00:24:05,833 --> 00:24:08,400
There's no basis for
what Selena is saying.

458
00:24:08,867 --> 00:24:13,700
And another thing, hunches
aren't accepted in the Court.

459
00:24:17,967 --> 00:24:21,300
Why, Sir? Do you think
Boss is that clean?

460
00:24:22,233 --> 00:24:24,933
That he doesn't hide any stench,
even a little?

461
00:24:26,833 --> 00:24:29,000
We all hide some stench,
Enriquez.

462
00:24:32,700 --> 00:24:34,733
But that's not important
anymore.

463
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:37,767
Only evidence is the truth,

464
00:24:39,167 --> 00:24:40,800
not our opinions.

465
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:01,400
So Boss paid you

466
00:25:01,533 --> 00:25:02,967
to throw eggs at the Mayor?

467
00:25:03,133 --> 00:25:04,867
Whatever Boss gave you,

468
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,700
- I'll triple it.
- What favor you will give me?

469
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:08,733
Tonyo, Son, I heard
from your Chief

470
00:25:08,867 --> 00:25:11,200
that there was a shootout
at the safehouse.

471
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:12,200
Are you okay?

472
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:13,367
<i> Let's talk some other time.</i>

473
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:15,100
Sir, who are you talking to?

474
00:25:15,233 --> 00:25:17,300
This has nothing to do with you,
Enriquez.

475
00:25:17,433 --> 00:25:20,033
Why can't you entertain the idea

476
00:25:20,167 --> 00:25:23,233
that Boss could have done
all this?

477
00:25:23,367 --> 00:25:25,200
You know, Boss won the debate.

478
00:25:25,333 --> 00:25:27,400
I have a favorite of his,
women's rights.

479
00:25:27,533 --> 00:25:29,300
Women's rights?
When he was famous,

480
00:25:29,433 --> 00:25:30,900
he hurt a woman.

481
00:25:31,033 --> 00:25:33,700
Are you saying that Boss
has a criminal record?

482
00:25:33,833 --> 00:25:35,200
I've been to the house of two
targets,

483
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:36,133
but there are a lot of pests.

484
00:25:36,267 --> 00:25:37,267
Just don't move

485
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,200
while the policewoman is there,
clear?

486
00:25:39,333 --> 00:25:42,033
Tonyo, can we talk?
